  <Docs>
    <summary>
            Provides an abstraction for adding default HTTP caching headers to a given <see cref="T:System.Net.Http.HttpResponseMessage" />.
            If no HTTP caching headers have been set on a response then this abstraction is called allowing for a default
            set of HTTP caching headers to be applied. By default, the <see cref="T:Microsoft.Azure.Mobile.Server.Cache.CachePolicyProvider" /> implementation is 
            registered with the dependency injection engine but other implementations can be registered as well. If
            no <see cref="T:Microsoft.Azure.Mobile.Server.Cache.ICachePolicyProvider" /> is registered then no default caching headers will be added to an
            <see cref="T:System.Net.Http.HttpResponseMessage" />.
            </summary>
